/PGMAòARIV/XX134/XX/PR

/KAYIGDAL / GREAT IS . . ./PR

/ITThis translation can be sung to the same melody as the Hebrew./PR

/PR

Great is the living God,/PR


to whom we give our praise,/PR

who is, and whose great being/PR


is timeless, without days./PR

the One, to whom in oneness/PR


no one can compare,/PR

invisible, in unity/PR


unbounded, everywhere,/PR

/PR

Who has no bodyòs form,/PR


has no material dress,/PR

nor can we find the likeness/PR


of Godòs awesome holiness,/PR

more ancient than all things/PR


brought forth in creation,/PR

the first of everything that is,/PR


Beginning unbegun!/PR

/PR

Behold the supreme being,/PR


whose universal power,/PR

whose greatness and whose rule/PR


all creatures shall declare,/PR

whose flow of prophecy/PR


was granted to a few,/PR

the treasured ones who stood amid/PR


Godòs splendor ever new./PI/PR

